Measurement.SummaryText.Websites.Anomaly:
On {date}, {WebsiteURL} presented signs of {BlockingReason} on {network} in {country}.

This might mean that {WebsiteURL} was blocked, but false positives can occur. 

Please explore the network measurement data below.

Measurement.Details.SummaryText.Telegram:
On {date}, Telegram was reachable on {network} in {country}. 

OONI's Telegram test successfully connected to Telegram's endpoints and web interface (web.telegram.org).

On {date}, the testing of Telegram's mobile app presented signs of blocking on {network} in {country}.

This might mean that Telegram's mobile app was blocked, but false positives can occur. 

Please explore the network measurement data below. Check other Telegram measurements from the same network during the same time period (if they're available).

On {date}, the testing of Telegram's web interface (web.telegram.org) presented signs of blocking on {network} in {country}.

This might mean that web.telegram.org was blocked, but false positives can occur.

Please explore the network measurement data below. Check other Telegram measurements from the same network during the same time period (if they're available).

On {date}, the testing of Telegram's mobile app and web interface (web.telegram.org) presented signs of blocking on {network} in {country}.

This might mean that both Telegram's mobile app and web interface were blocked, but false positives can occur.

Please explore the network measurement data below. Check other Telegram measurements from the same network during the same time period (if they're available).

Measurement.Details.SummaryText.TorVanil:
On {date}, OONI's Vanilla Tor test did not manage to bootstrap a connection to the [Tor network](https://www.torproject.org/).

This might mean that access to the Tor network was blocked on {network} in {country}, but false positives can occur.

Please explore the network measurement data below. Check other Tor measurements from the same network during the same time period (if they're available).

OONI's Vanilla Tor test successfully bootstrapped a connection to the [Tor network](https://www.torproject.org/).

This means that the Tor network was reachable from {network} in {country} on {date}.

Country.Overview.SummaryTextTemplate:
Thanks to OONI Probe users, {measurementCount} network measurements have been collected from {countryName} since {startDate}. These measurements cover {networkCovered} local networks. Most OONI Probe testing has been performed on {mostMeasuredASName}({mostMeasuredASNumber}).

Explore the data below to check the accessibility and/or blocking of sites and services.
Country.PeriodFilter.Label: Show results from
Country.Websites.Description:
Are websites blocked? If so, how?

The following results were collected through the use of OONI's [Web Connectivity test](https://ooni.io/nettest/web-connectivity/), designed to measure the DNS, HTTP, and TCP/IP blocking of websites. 

Most of the tested websites are included in the [Citizen Lab's test list repository](https://github.com/citizenlab/test-lists). If you'd like to see results on the testing of different websites, please [contribute to test lists](https://ooni.io/get-involved/contribute-test-lists/) or test the sites of your choice via the [OONI Probe mobile app](https://ooni.io/install/). 

Please note that unless a block page is served, some anomalous measurements may contain false positives. We therefore encourage you to examine anomalous measurements in depth and over time.
Country.Websites.BlockedByCategory.Descr: Websites that fall under the following categories were blocked on the {selectedASN} network.
Country.Apps.Description:
Are instant messaging apps (like WhatsApp and Facebook Messenger) blocked? If so, do circumvention tools work?

The following results were collected through the use of [OONI Probe tests](https://ooni.io/nettest/), designed to measure the blocking of WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, and Telegram. We also share results on the testing of circumvention tools, like [Tor](https://www.torproject.org/).
Country.NetworkProperties.Description:
What is the speed and performance of networks?

The following results were collected through the use of OONI Probe's performance and middlebox tests. You can check the speed and performance of tested networks, as well as video streaming performance. 

You can also learn whether middleboxes were detected in tested networks. Middleboxes are network appliances that can be used for a variety of networking purposes (such as caching), but sometimes they're used to implement internet censorship and/or surveillance.

Home.About.SummaryText: OONI Explorer is an expanding resource on internet censorship, dynamically updated with new network measurements collected by [OONI Probe](https://ooni.io/install/) users around the world. Consisting of millions of network measurements collected from more than 200 countries, OONI Explorer sheds light on internet censorship and other forms of network interference worldwide.
